1. Extract the Private Key (KEY File) 
Run the following command to extract the private key. You will be prompted for the original .p12 password, and then you must create a new password to encrypt the extracted key. 
bash
openssl pkcs12 -in yourfile.p12 -nocerts -out client.key
Use code with caution.
2. Extract the Certificate (CRT File) 
Run this command to extract the certificate. You will only need to enter the original .p12 password. 
bash
openssl pkcs12 -in yourfile.p12 -clcerts -nokeys -out client.crt
